description: [Capital FM] Naivasha -- The African Union Inter-African Bureau for Animal Resources (AU-IBAR),with the funding of the Bill &amp; Melinda Gates Foundation, is hosting a four-day high-level workshop in Naivasha, in a significant step towards transforming Africa's pastoral economy
title: Africa: AU-Ibar Hosts High-Level Workshop to Transform Pastoral Livestock Markets Across Africa

description: [Leadership] ASR Africa has conferred the "Abdul Samad Rabiu Achievers Awards" on 40 mentees from its mentorship programme in Al-Qalam University, Katsina State.
title: Africa: ASR Africa Confers Awards On Mentees

description: [CAF] Morocco are well on course to qualifying for the knockout stages of the CAF Beach Soccer Africa Cup of Nations Egypt 2024 after securing their second win of Group A on Monday, 21 October in Hurghada.
title: Africa: Morocco Make It Two in a Row With Win Over Ghana

description: [Ethiopian Herald] The Horn of Africa, a region rife with historical tensions and geopolitical complexities, appears increasingly vulnerable to destabilization. Central to this turmoil is Egypt, whose focus seems more aligned with its interests in the Arab world than with fostering constructive relationships in Africa.
title: Africa: Unholy Alliance With Boomerang Repercussion

description: [Vanguard] Innovate Africa Foundation in collaboration with Interswitch Group, Silicon Valley Product Group (SVPG), and WorkNigeria, have concluded the 2024 Inspire Africa Conference, the largest gathering of local and international product professionals in Africa.
title: Africa: Innovate Africa, Interswitch, Others Team Up for Inspire Africa Conference

description: [ISS] Rwanda-DRC talks have resumed, but whether they can shift the fundamental barriers to peace remains to be seen.
title: Africa: The Revived Luanda Process - Inching Towards Peace in East DRC?

description: [United Nations Biodiversity Conference] With some 23,000 pre-registered delegates representing almost every country on Earth, today's ceremonial opening of the 16th Conference of the Parties under the Convention on Biological Diversity (CBD COP 16) marks the arrival of a critical moment for biodiversity.
title: Africa: World Takes Crucial Step to Make Peace with Nature

description: [CAF] As the head coach of Commercial Bank of Ethiopia (CBE), Heye Gizaw Birhanu has led his team to a historic triumph in the CAF Women's Champions League CECAFA qualifiers.
title: Africa: CBE Coach Birhanu - We Want to Surprise Africa At the CAF Women's Champions League

description: [RFI] Made up of hundreds of discarded toys, household items, broken cables and bits of plastic, Cameroonian artist Malam's giant head-shaped sculptures are deceptively playful. Invited to the Also Known as Africa contemporary art and design fair (AKAA) in Paris, the artist says his giant installations are in fact a harsh critique of society's obsessive consumerism and disregard for the environment.
title: Africa: Malam, an Artist Taking the Idea of a 'Collection' to a New Level

description: [WHO] The World Health Organization (WHO) has certified Egypt as malaria-free, marking a significant public health milestone for a country with more than 100 million inhabitants. The achievement follows a nearly 100-year effort by the Egyptian government and people to end a disease that has been present in the country since ancient times.
title: Africa: Egypt Is Certified Malaria-Free By WHO

description: [ANGOP] Luanda -- The special envoy of the chairperson of the African Union Commission for Women, Peace and Security, Bineta Diop, made a positive assessment of the high-level forum of women in the Great Lakes Region on Saturday in Luanda.
title: Africa: AU Gives Positive Grade On Women's High-Level Forum of Great Lakes Region

description: [VOA] Nairobi, Kenya -- Africa has seen the capacity of its ports grow significantly over the years, but a report from the Africa Finance Corporation says the expansions, upgrades and investments have not led to better inland logistics and supply chains.
title: Africa: African Port Growth Hindered By Poor Road, Rail Networks, Report Says

description: [People's Dispatch] On World Food Day, activists from PHM South Africa held a picket, protesting soaring prices of healthy food
title: Africa: Health Activists Picket Against High Cost of Nutritious Food On World Food Day

description: [Afropop] Are you passionate about African and African diaspora music and culture? Do you thrive in the vibrant arts scene of New York City? Join Afropop Worldwide, the Peabody Award-winning leader in showcasing music and culture from Africa and the diaspora since 1988!
title: Africa: Afropop Worldwide - Now Hiring - Community Liaison Associate

description: [The Conversation Africa] Vaccinating older people probably did avert some deaths in 2021, but the effects were small. And even those small effects on mortality seem to have dissipated during the booster programme. That's the conclusion of our new study, published in the European Economic Review.
title: Africa: Vaccinating Care Home Residents Reduced Deaths, but the Effect Was Small - New Study

description: [Africa Renewal] At CHAC 2024, African countries seek to advocate for tailored solutions, mobilize resources, and influence global policies to address their unique challenges and build resilience
title: Africa: Examining Africa's Climate-Disease Connection
